  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Menstrual Pads For Dignity Initiative seeks to provide hygiene education and free washable menstrual kits that will last three years to 500 needy girls in Bunkpurugu/Yunyoo the most deprived district in Ghana to curb the high rates of menstruation-related absenteeism among junior and senior high school girls thus impacting directly on the Millennium Development Goals MDG 3(gender equality) and keeping girls in school (MDG 2).</narrative>
  </description>
